<p>
<a name="location">@HI{{@EM{{de}}}}</a> indicates the location of an action. Note that it normally cannot
indicate location of existence except in the case where it is used with @HI{{aru}} to locate an event.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kinou@FG{{@KJ{{silver^sit}}:ginza}}no@KT{{resutorann}}@EM{{de}}@KJ{{nightfall}}gohanwo@KJ{{eat}}bemashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yesterday I had dinner at a restaurant in Ginza.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="means">@HI{{@EM{{de}}}}</a> indicates a means or an implement.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{day^book}}he@KJ{{boat}}@EM{{de}}@KJ{{come}}mashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I came to Japan by boat.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="materials">@HI{{@EM{{de}}}}</a> indicates the materials used.
Note that @HI{{@EM{{de}}}} must be used if the raw material is obvious from the final product, otherwise
@HI{{@EM{{de}}}} may be replaced by <a href="grammar-particle-kara.html">@HI{{kara}}</a>.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono @KT{{ke-ki}}ha,@KJ{{egg}}to@KJ{{sugar}}@EM{{de}}@KJ{{make}}rimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This cake is made of butter and eggs.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="comparison">@HI{{@EM{{de}}}}</a> indicates the greatest, least etc. in a comparison.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{generation^world}}@EM{{de}}@KJ{{one^turn^tall}}i@KJ{{mountain}}ha@KJ{{what}}desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What is the tallest mountain in the world?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="quantity">@HI{{@EM{{de}}}}</a> indicates the amount and scope.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{book}}ha1@KJ{{time^interval}}@EM{{de}}@KJ{{read}}memasuyo.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      You can read this book in an hour.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="condition">@HI{{@EM{{de}}}}</a> indicates the mode or condition of the agent of an action.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{mountain^rice*field}}sanha@KT{{apa-to}}ni1@KJ{{person}}@EM{{de}}@KJ{{dwell}}ndeimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yamada lives in an apartment by himself.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="time">@HI{{@EM{{de}}}}</a> indicates time or age.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{poem^person}}ha25@KJ{{year-end}}@EM{{de}}@KJ{{death}}nda.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      That poet died at 25.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="cause">@HI{{@EM{{de}}}}</a> indicates the reason for something.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{ill^spirit}}@EM{{de}}@KJ{{trip^going}}ni@KJ{{going}}kenakatta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Because I was ill, I couldn't go on the trip.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRNDEND{{}}

